The culture of having an ‘all-nighter' still exists, he said, and added that modern technology and increasing pressure on students are raising the problem of sleep deprivation.
Making sure you have enough sleep, of good quality, should serve as a ‘secret weapon' for students to fight stress, extreme fatigue and anxiety, he says - also to prevent weight gain, because sleep deprivation puts the brain in a state of hunger, so they become constantly hungry.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old Californian who studies chemical and physical biology, helped Professor Czeisler design the course, after taking a class he had in his first year at Harvard.
He said his eyes were open and he had the inspiration to pursue a schooling course.
